Here&#39;s a solution that prints the first variable `a`, `b` number of times as desired. The program also makes an arbitrary check `b &gt; 0` to ensure that the result can be expressed in an expanded form.

	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);

	    System.out.println(&quot;Enter an integer: &quot;);
	    int a = input.nextInt();
	    System.out.println(&quot;What power do you want &quot; + a + &quot; to be raised to? &quot;);
	    int b = input.nextInt();

	    if (b &gt; 0) {
	        System.out.print(a);
	        for (int i = 1; i &lt; b; i++)
	        	System.out.print(&quot; x &quot; + a);
	    } else {
            System.out.println(a + &quot;^&quot; + b + &quot; cannot be expanded!&quot;);
        }
	}

